Wonderful, warm woman.

254
00:17:44,949 --> 00:17:46,541
And then, one day...

255
00:17:46,789 --> 00:17:50,782
...she turned into this amazing creature
who could sit on a broomstick...

256
00:17:51,989 --> 00:17:54,344
...and take off into the air.

257
00:17:54,869 --> 00:17:56,939
She could actually achieve flight.

258
00:17:57,749 --> 00:17:59,740
I think I was married to that lady once.

259
00:17:59,829 --> 00:18:00,944
Small world.

260
00:18:01,309 --> 00:18:03,265
Funny thing is, this happened...

261
00:18:03,589 --> 00:18:07,218
...the same time I went completely deaf.
Isn't that a coincidence?

262
00:18:07,309 --> 00:18:09,300
Amazing. Who'd believe it?

263
00:18:10,309 --> 00:18:13,221
What do you want out of life
before the show's over?

264
00:18:15,269 --> 00:18:17,703
Just not to make a fool out of myself.

265
00:18:18,869 --> 00:18:20,382
That's all you want?

266
00:18:20,909 --> 00:18:22,865
I have this terrible fear...

267
00:18:23,869 --> 00:18:25,666
...that I'll make a mistake...

268
00:18:26,149 --> 00:18:28,219
...and everyone'll stand around...

269
00:18:29,029 --> 00:18:30,462
...and stare at me.

270
00:18:30,709 --> 00:18:32,301
Boy, damn!

271
00:18:32,789 --> 00:18:34,859
I wish I had met you eight years ago.

272
00:18:34,949 --> 00:18:37,509
I can fix your problems in ten seconds.

273
00:18:37,669 --> 00:18:38,818
Ten seconds?

274
00:18:39,109 --> 00:18:41,942
Ten seconds, if you trust me.
Do you trust me?

275
00:18:45,949 --> 00:18:47,382
Sure.

276
00:18:55,429 --> 00:18:57,147
You're a good-looking guy.

277
00:18:57,389 --> 00:18:59,778
Thank you. That's very kind of you.

278
00:19:02,949 --> 00:19:04,541
How's that feel? Good?

279
00:19:05,949 --> 00:19:07,826
You look a little silly to me.

280
00:19:08,309 --> 00:19:09,583
Kind of foolish.

281
00:19:12,549 --> 00:19:15,427
You see, life ain't so complicated.

282
00:19:34,109 --> 00:19:36,828
-When's the next one coming?
-Any second.

283
00:19:37,909 --> 00:19:39,865
That might be the truck coming now.

284
00:19:39,949 --> 00:19:42,019
I have to go get a damn screwdriver.

285
00:19:46,349 --> 00:19:47,862
The blind guy around?

286
00:19:56,749 --> 00:19:58,307
Where's the blind guy?

287
00:19:58,509 --> 00:20:00,864
-Who do you want?
-Kerew. Wally Kerew.

288
00:20:01,309 --> 00:20:03,584
I'm his bookie. I owe him some money.

289
00:20:06,349 --> 00:20:09,068
He's waiting for a delivery.
He'll be back in a minute.

290
00:20:09,149 --> 00:20:10,468
Is he out front?

291
00:20:10,909 --> 00:20:12,308
I'll go find him.

292
00:20:17,469 --> 00:20:19,539
I almost forgot. I need some....

293
00:20:22,029 --> 00:20:26,227
-We're not officially open yet.
-I know. I need some of that stuff up there.

294
00:20:26,949 --> 00:20:29,827
My tummy's all kaput.
What is that stuff up there?

295
00:20:30,469 --> 00:20:32,107
-What, the antacid?
-Yes.

296
00:20:32,989 --> 00:20:36,425
What's the difference between
Alka-Seltzer and the one next to it?

297
00:20:36,509 --> 00:20:37,498
Di-Gel?

298
00:20:38,269 --> 00:20:40,829
Do me a favour.
Can you read it to me, please?

299
00:20:41,069 --> 00:20:45,108
-You want me to read out Di-Gel?
-Yeah, my eyes ain't too good.

300
00:20:46,709 --> 00:20:47,824
Jesus.

301
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:55,543
"Di-Gel contains calcium carbonate,
an effective antacid...."

302
00:20:57,269 --> 00:20:58,418
Where you going?

303
00:20:58,509 --> 00:21:01,945
Here, take it. Honestly,
I wasn't trying to pull anything.

304
00:21:02,349 --> 00:21:05,261
You were told to deliver this
right from the airport.

305
00:21:05,349 --> 00:21:07,738
I thought I was being tailed by the cops.

306
00:21:07,829 --> 00:21:10,218
I didn't want to bring them
near Mr. Sutherland.

307
00:21:10,309 --> 00:21:11,708
You gotta tell him that.

308
00:21:11,789 --> 00:21:14,667
You tell him that.
I have a car waiting out front.

309
00:21:15,109 --> 00:21:16,827
I'm dead if I go with you.

310
00:21:17,029 --> 00:21:19,224
You're dead if you don't go with me.

311
00:21:26,789 --> 00:21:30,748
"Bubbles of gas, trapped in the stomach,
can cause heartburn...

312
00:21:30,829 --> 00:21:33,821
"...acid indigestion
and that full, bloated feeling.

313
00:21:34,189 --> 00:21:36,066
"And unlike plain antacids...

314
00:21:36,309 --> 00:21:39,904
"...the simethicone breaks up
gas bubbles rapidly...

315
00:21:40,469 --> 00:21:44,257
"...to relieve fullness and pressure."
I feel like a commercial.

316
00:21:58,669 --> 00:22:00,580
What the hell was that?

317
00:22:01,229 --> 00:22:02,378
Wait a minute.

318
00:22:02,469 --> 00:22:04,585
Wait my ass! I thought I heard....

319
00:22:09,469 --> 00:22:11,346
What is this? Hide-and-seek?

320
00:22:24,189 --> 00:22:26,908
-This guy is dead.
-Wally, there's a gun here.

321
00:22:27,669 --> 00:22:28,897
Don't touch it!

322
00:22:30,549 --> 00:22:31,538
Freeze!

323
00:22:31,869 --> 00:22:33,461
Drop it! I said drop it!

324
00:22:33,549 --> 00:22:35,779
-What is he saying?
-Are you holding a weapon?

325
00:22:35,869 --> 00:22:36,904
Yes, I am.

326
00:22:37,029 --> 00:22:38,940
Throw it away! Get rid of it!

327
00:22:40,069 --> 00:22:41,468
-Stay there!
-Freeze!

328
00:22:41,549 --> 00:22:44,188
-Don't shoot!
-Don't move or we'll blow your brains out.

329
00:22:44,269 --> 00:22:45,497
-Wait!
-Shut up!

330
00:22:46,189 --> 00:22:47,542
Please, be gentle.

331
00:22:48,749 --> 00:22:49,784
Let's go.

332
00:22:50,349 --> 00:22:52,544
-I had nothing to do with this.
-Let's go!

333
00:22:52,629 --> 00:22:55,063
Officer, he came for Alka-Seltzer.

334
00:22:55,149 --> 00:22:58,380
The man asked me to read him
a Di-Gel label, can you believe that?

335
00:22:58,469 --> 00:23:00,425
We don't even know the man.

336
00:23:01,069 --> 00:23:03,663
Wally, get the money from the cigar box.

337
00:23:04,509 --> 00:23:09,503
Officer, excuse me. Honest to God,
isn't there a nice way we can settle this?

338
00:23:09,629 --> 00:23:11,028
Can I at least get my coat?

339
00:23:11,109 --> 00:23:12,986
Hang on. We'll get your coat.

340
00:23:14,629 --> 00:23:17,780
Tell Mr. Huddleston to lock up for us.

341
00:23:41,469 --> 00:23:42,902
Let's move out.

342
00:23:49,269 --> 00:23:52,705
You can't say whether
this mystery woman fired the shot or not?

343
00:23:52,829 --> 00:23:54,820
No, but if she was innocent...

344
00:23:54,909 --> 00:23:57,821
...why did she leave
right after the shot was fired?

345
00:23:58,069 --> 00:23:59,821
-That makes sense.
-Gatlin.

346
00:24:04,069 --> 00:24:07,948
What's the story?
The Commissioner is crawling up my ass!

347
00:24:08,629 --> 00:24:10,824
The whole thing sounds kind of shaky.

348
00:24:10,909 --> 00:24:13,298
The deaf guy's not sure about the woman.

349
00:24:13,389 --> 00:24:17,143
The blind guy heard the shot,
but can't make an identification.

350
00:24:17,229 --> 00:24:19,823
You're feeling too damn sorry for them.

351
00:24:19,989 --> 00:24:23,379
You're always feeling sorry for people,
that's your trouble.

352
00:24:23,469 --> 00:24:25,107
I'll take care of this.

353
00:24:32,109 --> 00:24:35,385
Now we're gonna quit fucking around here
and start talking serious.

354
00:24:35,469 --> 00:24:37,778
Now you claim
there was a woman present.

355
00:24:39,869 --> 00:24:41,780
Was there a woman present?

356
00:24:44,789 --> 00:24:46,507
Was there a woman present?

357
00:24:46,669 --> 00:24:48,341
I'm sorry. You talking to me?

358
00:24:48,429 --> 00:24:51,466
You bet your ass I'm talking to you.
Was there or wasn't there?

359
00:24:51,549 --> 00:24:53,380
Was there or wasn't there what?

360
00:24:53,469 --> 00:24:55,061
A woman present.

361
00:24:55,149 --> 00:24:58,266
I smelled a woman,
but I didn't see a woman.

362
00:24:59,789 --> 00:25:03,498
What about you, wiseass?
Was there or wasn't there a woman?

363
00:25:05,189 --> 00:25:09,467
What the hell do I have to do,
take you to a private room and ask you?

364
00:25:10,149 --> 00:25:13,027
He's deaf. You have to be facing him.

365
00:25:15,309 --> 00:25:18,221
No more bullshit!
Was there or wasn't there a woman?

366
00:25:18,749 --> 00:25:21,661
-Are you serious?
-Yes, I'm goddamn serious.

367
00:25:21,989 --> 00:25:24,025
Fuzzy Wuzzy was a woman?

368
00:25:24,669 --> 00:25:26,421
What the hell is he talking about?

369
00:25:26,509 --> 00:25:28,898
He reads lips. You're talking too fast.

370
00:25:32,789 --> 00:25:34,780
Was there...

371
00:25:34,949 --> 00:25:37,258
...a woman...

372
00:25:37,709 --> 00:25:38,983
...present?

373
00:25:39,549 --> 00:25:40,538
Yes.

374
00:25:40,989 --> 00:25:43,105
There was...

375
00:25:43,549 --> 00:25:46,939
...a woman...

376
00:25:47,789 --> 00:25:49,586
...present.

377
00:25:50,269 --> 00:25:51,861
Why is he talking like that?

378
00:25:51,949 --> 00:25:54,588
Because he's deaf...

379
00:25:55,189 --> 00:25:57,419
...not stupid.

380
00:26:00,949 --> 00:26:04,862
Can you tell me one goddamn thing
about that woman?

381
00:26:05,349 --> 00:26:08,659
She has the most magnificent legs
I've ever seen in my life.

382
00:26:08,829 --> 00:26:11,389
Yeah, and she smells good, too.

383
00:26:12,829 --> 00:26:15,866
Don't tell me you didn't hear anything,
'cause he heard it!

384
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:18,941
And you, don't tell me
you didn't see anything 'cause he saw it.

385
00:26:19,029 --> 00:26:22,339
Between the two of you,
you saw and heard everything.

386
00:26:23,149 --> 00:26:27,267
Some poor bastard's dead,
so start answering some questions here!

387
00:26:27,869 --> 00:26:29,587
-Excuse me, Captain?
-What!

388
00:26:29,669 --> 00:26:34,060
Professor Kasuda from uptown.
You'll be interested in his ballistics report.

389
00:26:34,229 --> 00:26:35,457
What do you got?

390
00:26:35,549 --> 00:26:39,906
I think I can prove to a judge
that both of these men had the mens rea.

391
00:26:40,909 --> 00:26:42,900
What the hell is a mens rea?

392
00:26:43,189 --> 00:26:45,623
It's a legal term the lawyers use.

393
00:26:45,749 --> 00:26:48,627
It just means
the intention to commit a crime.

394
00:26:48,949 --> 00:26:51,304
-Okay, come on, let's go.
-Mens rea?

395
00:26:51,389 --> 00:26:52,617
Put the cuffs on them.

396
00:26:52,709 --> 00:26:54,381
How could we have gotten mens rea?

397
00:26:54,469 --> 00:26:56,425
-Don't worry.
-Come on, get up, will ya?

398
00:26:56,509 --> 00:26:59,103
-Did we take blood?
-Get up, for crying out loud!

399
00:26:59,189 --> 00:27:00,702
Please rise.

400
00:27:01,109 --> 00:27:03,100
Can you do it without taking blood?

401
00:27:03,189 --> 00:27:06,022
Stupid, he's deaf.
You have to be facing him!

402
00:27:06,109 --> 00:27:08,907
The lab says that gun you were holding
was the death weapon.

403
00:27:08,989 --> 00:27:11,219
We both use condoms.
How is this possible?

404
00:27:11,309 --> 00:27:13,948
-I want to see a lawyer.
-That's not all Mr. Kerew.

405
00:27:14,029 --> 00:27:15,747
-I want a doctor.
-We found something...

406
00:27:15,829 --> 00:27:18,059
...in the apartment
of the deceased Mr. Scotto.

407
00:27:18,149 --> 00:27:19,628
Joey Scotto!

408
00:27:20,989 --> 00:27:23,947
We found your name
on a marker in Mr. Scotto's wallet.

409
00:27:24,029 --> 00:27:27,226
"W. Kerew, $2,800, overdue."

410
00:27:27,309 --> 00:27:29,777
-Because I owe him money?
-I feel sick.

411
00:27:30,349 --> 00:27:32,863
You owe the guy $3,000
he comes to bust your head...

412
00:27:32,949 --> 00:27:34,940
...and your boyfriend lets him have it.

413
00:27:35,029 --> 00:27:36,906
He is not my boyfriend.

414
00:27:36,989 --> 00:27:38,308
Mens rea!

415
00:27:41,069 --> 00:27:43,025
My God! No!

416
00:27:47,029 --> 00:27:48,144
Chequebook.

417
00:27:48,349 --> 00:27:49,464
Knife.

418
00:27:51,629 --> 00:27:53,142
Racing forms.

419
00:27:53,709 --> 00:27:55,222
A pair of undershorts.

420
00:27:56,349 --> 00:27:57,702
And a ticket...

421
00:28:00,229 --> 00:28:02,459
...to EI Paso, Texas. It's not here!

422
00:28:28,069 --> 00:28:29,297
No coin.

423
00:28:30,149 --> 00:28:33,221
-I wish I hadn't killed him.
-If you had to, you had to.

424
00:28:34,349 --> 00:28:38,262
We know he had it at the airport,
he must've made a switchover somewhere.

425
00:28:38,629 --> 00:28:41,462
The man who owns the news-stand,
his name is David Lyons.

426
00:28:41,549 --> 00:28:43,904
He was talking to Scotto when I arrived.

427
00:28:44,109 --> 00:28:46,225
Would he be able to identify you?

428
00:28:46,589 --> 00:28:49,899
No, he never saw me. Also, he's deaf.

429
00:28:50,709 --> 00:28:51,937
Deaf?

430
00:28:53,469 --> 00:28:55,824
And the other one is blind.

431
00:28:56,389 --> 00:28:58,539
Blind? Deaf? What is this, a joke?

432
00:28:59,029 --> 00:29:00,303
No joke.

433
00:29:00,389 --> 00:29:04,701
-I spoke with the building superintendent.
-Let's pay them a visit, shall we?

434
00:29:06,109 --> 00:29:07,588
They're in jail now.

435
00:29:08,029 --> 00:29:10,145
Then let's bail them out.

436
00:29:13,789 --> 00:29:17,498
All right, Mr. Lyons,
I need a nice full face shot first.

437
00:29:17,949 --> 00:29:20,417
Then we'll get our side shots later.

438
00:29:20,549 --> 00:29:21,538
You ready?

439
00:29:21,629 --> 00:29:24,541
We're here because you owed
that sleazeball $2,800?

440
00:29:24,709 --> 00:29:26,381
Face forward, please.

441
00:29:26,469 --> 00:29:30,667
I thought the Knicks would beat Boston,
and they came damn close.

442
00:29:30,909 --> 00:29:33,423
Tell your friend to face the front, please.

443
00:29:33,509 --> 00:29:34,624
Face front.

444
00:29:35,509 --> 00:29:38,023
-What do you need a bookie for?
-Credit.

445
00:29:38,269 --> 00:29:41,147
-Face front, please.
-No one else would give me credit.

446
00:29:41,229 --> 00:29:44,938
-Face front.
-Will you tell him to hold still, please?

447
00:29:45,469 --> 00:29:46,868
Hold still.

448
00:29:50,309 --> 00:29:51,583
What's he doing?

449
00:29:52,069 --> 00:29:53,297
Holding still.

450
00:29:54,429 --> 00:29:56,704
Not looking at you, looking at me!

451
00:29:59,189 --> 00:30:00,702
Face the camera.

452
00:30:01,789 --> 00:30:03,780
Perfect. Tell him not to move.

453
00:30:04,109 --> 00:30:05,622
-What?
-Don't move.

454
00:30:06,669 --> 00:30:08,500
I'm getting fed up with her.

455
00:30:10,149 --> 00:30:11,901
Why is he doing this to me?

456
00:30:12,109 --> 00:30:14,259
I just want him to face the camera!

457
00:30:14,469 --> 00:30:16,778
-He's not facing the camera?
-No!

458
00:30:17,189 --> 00:30:18,907
It's news to me.

459
00:30:19,309 --> 00:30:21,220
-What?
-Face the camera.

460
00:30:22,749 --> 00:30:25,058
That's better. Hold it.

461
00:30:25,189 --> 00:30:27,623
-She should make up her mind.
-Shit!

462
00:30:28,309 --> 00:30:29,378
Shit!

463
00:30:30,269 --> 00:30:31,588
Shit!

464
00:30:33,189 --> 00:30:36,545
-Is she saying shit or ship?
-Shit.

465
00:30:40,549 --> 00:30:42,983
Why would she say "ship"?

466
00:30:44,269 --> 00:30:48,182
-It wouldn't make any sense.
-Get him out of here. I want him out, now!

467
00:30:49,389 --> 00:30:52,301
You're finished.
I'll get you when you're sleeping.

468
00:30:52,989 --> 00:30:56,379
We'll be all right. Once they find
that woman, they'll let us out.

469
00:30:56,469 --> 00:30:59,108
What woman?
They're not looking for no woman.

470
00:30:59,189 --> 00:31:01,578
They got their killers. Us. We're fucked!

471
00:31:01,669 --> 00:31:03,182
Captain, honestly....

472
00:31:04,189 --> 00:31:06,749
-You all right?
-What the hell's wrong with you?

473
00:31:06,829 --> 00:31:09,423
Can't you walk?
What do we have to do, carry you?

474
00:31:09,509 --> 00:31:11,067
You don't have to do shit for me.

475
00:31:11,149 --> 00:31:13,344
He's blind and you have him handcuffed!

476
00:31:13,429 --> 00:31:15,420
Come on, for crying out loud.

477
00:31:15,589 --> 00:31:19,821
All right, take the cuffs off him
before he wrecks the goddamn joint.

478
00:31:20,109 --> 00:31:21,747
Don't do me no favours.

479
00:31:22,109 --> 00:31:24,100
Is everybody happy now?

480
00:31:24,309 --> 00:31:27,745
Are we all friends again?
Come on now, let's go.

481
00:31:29,709 --> 00:31:33,861
Joe, I got Lyons, David;
Kerew, Wallace, suspected homicide.

482
00:31:34,349 --> 00:31:35,907
His lawyers are here, Captain.

483
00:31:35,989 --> 00:31:38,059
-Whose?
-David Lyons.

484
00:31:38,269 --> 00:31:39,907
My lawyers?

485
00:31:40,429 --> 00:31:42,989
You want to check him for police brutality?

486
00:31:43,149 --> 00:31:46,141
You got as long as it takes to print him.
Get in here.

487
00:31:47,829 --> 00:31:50,980
-I know you don't know who we are.
-Your right hand, please.

488
00:31:51,069 --> 00:31:54,300
Our law firm represents
the building you have your shop in.

489
00:31:54,509 --> 00:31:57,342
We've been sent here
to try to arrange bail for you.

490
00:31:57,429 --> 00:31:59,385
-Great.
-That's a nice surprise.

491
00:31:59,869 --> 00:32:03,862
They can only hold you and Mr. Kerew
up to 72 hours before an arraignment.

492
00:32:04,309 --> 00:32:06,948
With luck,
we'll have you out of here by 5:00.

493
00:32:07,189 --> 00:32:10,625
We're pushing the blind and deaf angle.
We hope you don't mind.

494
00:32:10,709 --> 00:32:12,665
No, we don't mind. Use it.

495
00:32:12,749 --> 00:32:14,740
We'll see you both very soon.

496
00:32:15,109 --> 00:32:17,498
Excuse me, miss, have we met before?

497
00:32:20,149 --> 00:32:21,821
No, I don't think so.

498
00:32:21,909 --> 00:32:24,218
Are you wearing Shalimar perfume?

499
00:32:26,309 --> 00:32:27,901
