01:27:10,109 --> 01:27:11,622
Surely, my dear.

1227
01:27:11,989 --> 01:27:15,584
Mr. Kirgo decided at the last minute
to renegotiate his contract...

1228
01:27:15,669 --> 01:27:17,739
...and he put a pistol to my head.

1229
01:27:18,269 --> 01:27:20,829
Eve, we've been associated for five years.

1230
01:27:20,989 --> 01:27:24,265
I want you to know
I have no intention of killing you.

1231
01:27:24,709 --> 01:27:26,700
So don't be frightened, my dear.

1232
01:27:27,069 --> 01:27:29,503
Please, don't do anything rash.

1233
01:27:30,669 --> 01:27:33,979
No, I wouldn't do that.
You know I trust you, Mr. Sutherland.

1234
01:27:35,189 --> 01:27:37,020
But what are your intentions?

1235
01:27:37,469 --> 01:27:40,939
To leave the country as soon
as Raul sends my helicopter down.

1236
01:27:41,349 --> 01:27:43,226
I invite you to come along.

1237
01:27:43,629 --> 01:27:46,348
Rio can be captivating this time of year.

1238
01:27:47,269 --> 01:27:52,218
Just pick up the gold coin
I believe is on the floor in front of you.

1239
01:27:57,509 --> 01:27:58,703
I don't see it.

1240
01:27:59,549 --> 01:28:03,588
Look in Mr. Kirgo's left hand.
I think he may be holding it.

1241
01:28:09,509 --> 01:28:12,387
Did you find it, my dear?

1242
01:28:14,949 --> 01:28:16,177
I found it.

1243
01:28:17,349 --> 01:28:19,658
Would you hand it to me, please?

1244
01:28:22,469 --> 01:28:24,539
May I ask what my share might be?

1245
01:28:26,349 --> 01:28:27,418
One...

1246
01:28:28,509 --> 01:28:29,703
...half...

1247
01:28:30,429 --> 01:28:31,748
...of $8 million.

1248
01:28:32,589 --> 01:28:34,341
Would you say that's fair?

1249
01:28:36,949 --> 01:28:39,258
Yes, I think that's very fair.

1250
01:28:47,509 --> 01:28:48,783
What's going on?

1251
01:29:00,709 --> 01:29:02,347
What just happened?

1252
01:29:02,949 --> 01:29:05,463
Mr. Sutherland is no longer with us.

1253
01:29:08,789 --> 01:29:10,427
I'm right here, Wally.

1254
01:29:11,629 --> 01:29:14,826
I hear the sirens.
The police will be here soon.

1255
01:29:15,429 --> 01:29:19,104
Drop that pistol now and you'll make
license plates and play volleyball...

1256
01:29:19,189 --> 01:29:21,305
...every afternoon for a few years.

1257
01:29:21,949 --> 01:29:23,541
I'll even wait for you.

1258
01:29:24,469 --> 01:29:25,663
Thanks.

1259
01:29:26,109 --> 01:29:27,861
That's real sweet.

1260
01:29:28,349 --> 01:29:32,740
But you see,
you're the ones they're looking for.

1261
01:29:34,069 --> 01:29:35,263
Not me.

1262
01:29:35,829 --> 01:29:39,868
If I get on that helicopter with the coin,
I get out of here squeaky clean.

1263
01:29:41,349 --> 01:29:43,465
You're too tall for me anyway.

1264
01:29:44,629 --> 01:29:47,097
I'm afraid I'm gonna have to lock you in.

1265
01:29:47,909 --> 01:29:49,137
Sorry.

1266
01:29:52,789 --> 01:29:54,381
Damn, she smells good.

1267
01:29:55,709 --> 01:29:58,860
I hear jail ain't so bad,
if you like it up the butt.

1268
01:30:00,349 --> 01:30:02,783
-I'm over here, Wally.
-Over where, Dave?

1269
01:30:07,949 --> 01:30:10,782
Who am I talking to if he can't hear me?

1270
01:30:21,749 --> 01:30:25,822
-She's running to the helicopter.
-Nice air conditioning she made.

1271
01:30:28,309 --> 01:30:31,938
-Did you ever want to be in the circus?
-No. I'm afraid of heights.

1272
01:30:32,669 --> 01:30:35,024
-Give me your jacket, please.
-What for?

1273
01:30:36,029 --> 01:30:38,145
There we go. This should be fun. Ready?

1274
01:30:38,229 --> 01:30:42,188
-We're not high up, are we?
-No. We're just a few feet off the ground.

1275
01:30:42,549 --> 01:30:44,505
-Ready and go!
-I'm ready!

1276
01:30:50,309 --> 01:30:53,381
I just knocked over a tree!
You said we weren't up high!

1277
01:30:54,509 --> 01:30:56,022
I'll kill you, you fuck!

1278
01:30:57,869 --> 01:31:01,179
You're telling me we're not up in the air!
What do you mean?

1279
01:31:04,029 --> 01:31:06,668
Get ready. Bomb bay doors opening.

1280
01:31:08,549 --> 01:31:10,460
Get ready to fire one!

1281
01:31:11,949 --> 01:31:13,507
And fire one!

1282
01:31:16,229 --> 01:31:17,582
Fire two!

1283
01:31:41,349 --> 01:31:43,226
What the hell are you doing!

1284
01:31:43,309 --> 01:31:46,699
I don't know. I'm blind.
I learnt this at the Braille lnstitute.

1285
01:31:46,789 --> 01:31:49,781
They told us to feel around
and see what's happening.

1286
01:31:58,029 --> 01:31:59,462
Hold it right there!

1287
01:31:59,549 --> 01:32:01,858
I said hold it or I'll throw your brains out!

1288
01:32:01,949 --> 01:32:04,258
I'll throw this knife through your brain!

1289
01:32:04,349 --> 01:32:05,338
Freeze!

1290
01:32:06,749 --> 01:32:09,547
-Do what I say or you're a dead man.
-Turn around.

1291
01:32:11,589 --> 01:32:12,658
Face front.

1292
01:32:16,549 --> 01:32:19,302
That's better.
Now put your hands over your head.

1293
01:32:20,829 --> 01:32:22,785
-Come on.
-Get your hands up!

1294
01:32:23,829 --> 01:32:26,138
You do speak English. Come over here.

1295
01:32:28,269 --> 01:32:29,861
Get your ass over here.

1296
01:32:30,509 --> 01:32:31,464
Quickly.

1297
01:32:31,629 --> 01:32:32,948
-Slowly.
-Slowly.

1298
01:32:37,029 --> 01:32:38,508
Come on.

1299
01:32:40,069 --> 01:32:41,787
Not now, Wally, I'm busy.

1300
01:32:43,069 --> 01:32:46,459
Keep coming, you funny little turd.

1301
01:32:47,629 --> 01:32:49,859
Tarzan, turn around and take a look.

1302
01:32:58,109 --> 01:33:01,784
-When did you guys get here?
-I sure was worried about you two.

1303
01:33:09,229 --> 01:33:10,947
Good-bye, Captain Braddock.

1304
01:33:13,189 --> 01:33:15,464
Captain Braddock, you're a dickhead.

1305
01:33:16,189 --> 01:33:17,702
You son of a bitch.

1306
01:33:18,989 --> 01:33:21,628
-I got a surprise for you.
-You can't do that.

1307
01:33:21,989 --> 01:33:24,298
I know the law. Now I get to shoot them!

1308
01:33:24,389 --> 01:33:26,425
-You can't.
-What do you mean I can't?

1309
01:33:26,509 --> 01:33:28,739
Captain, we got the real killer.

1310
01:33:30,069 --> 01:33:33,698
-You telling me that I can't shoot them?
-No, sir, you can't.

1311
01:33:34,549 --> 01:33:38,781
We went to all this trouble to catch them
and now I can't shoot them?

1312
01:33:39,469 --> 01:33:41,221
It's time to go.

1313
01:33:41,589 --> 01:33:43,466
But I want to shoot them.

1314
01:33:46,309 --> 01:33:48,140
We'll get some hot chocolate.

1315
01:33:48,709 --> 01:33:50,586
Why can't I shoot them?

1316
01:33:53,909 --> 01:33:56,628
-We had a damn good time, didn't we?
-Yeah.

1317
01:33:57,789 --> 01:33:59,427
A lot of nice memories.

1318
01:34:03,629 --> 01:34:07,747
Wally, there's something I've been
wanting to do since the day I met you.

1319
01:34:08,109 --> 01:34:10,748
-That was two days ago.
-That's right.

1320
01:34:12,469 --> 01:34:14,858
There's something I want to give you.

1321
01:34:15,069 --> 01:34:17,378
You don't have to give me anything.

1322
01:34:18,189 --> 01:34:19,781
You're a real nice guy.

1323
01:34:20,069 --> 01:34:21,946
But I want to give it to you.

1324
01:34:23,549 --> 01:34:26,985
-Listen to me. I have a lot of love for you.
-Thank you.

1325
01:34:32,109 --> 01:34:36,148
Tell me, how's it feel to be handicapped?
I always wanted to ask you that.

1326
01:34:36,789 --> 01:34:39,257
I'm not handicapped. I have you.

1327
01:34:55,589 --> 01:34:57,580
Subtitles by SOFTITLER

